The paper discusses deep learning methods in the context of natural language processing, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with the interaction between computers and human languages. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various model designs and methods, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the evolution of deep learning in NLP, which could also place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
